Dis-Chem JOHANNESBURG - South Africa experienced fewer cases of cold and flu under lockdown than in previous years. In its year to end-February results, pharmaceutical giant Dis-Chem says this is because more people have been working from home and practicing social distancing. It reports this has an impact on over-the-counter sales. But the group's strong chronic drug adherence campaigns partially offset this over the winter months. READ: Dis-Chem ready to administer vaccines Another change in consumer behaviour during the pandemic is a surge in online sales by over 260 percent. This doesn't mean the group did not get hurt by COVID-19. Under the hard lockdown, it faced trading restrictions which saw its cosmetic sales decline by 20 percent.